{
  "texts": [
    "However, there exists a significant domain gap between the virtual world and reality.",
    "Image generation methods can generate realistic scene images based on different control signals, such as HD maps [26,41,63], sketch layout [75], bounding boxes [26,41,67], text [26,34,41,67] and driving actions [34,67].",
    "However, these approaches can hardly maintain scene consistency.",
    "To obtain a coherent driving scene, methods based on scene rendering target to reconstruct the 3D scene.",
    "READ [42] employs point clouds and uses a U-Net to render images."
  ]
}